HEADWORD: Diprotodon
<hw>Di*pro"to*don</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>di-</grk> = <grk>di`s-</grk> twice + <?/ first +
<grk>'odoy`s</grk>, <grk>'odo`ntos</grk>, tooth.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An extinct Quaternary marsupial from
Australia, about as large as the hippopotamus; -- so named because of
its two large front teeth. See <xex>Illustration</xex> in
Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

